## 2. CONTENT DELIVERY NETWORK (CDN) - For Movie Files

### **Architecture Decision: CDN for Movie Distribution**
```
┌─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐
│        GLOBAL CDN NETWORK (CloudFlare / AWS CloudFront)         │
├──────────┬──────────────┬──────────┬──────────────┬──────────┤
│  US-EAST │  EUROPE     │  ASIA    │  SOUTH ASIA  │  LATAM   │
│ Edge #1  │  Edge #2    │ Edge #3  │   Edge #4    │ Edge #5  │
└──────────┴──────────────┴──────────┴──────────────┴──────────┘
                         │
                         ▼
┌─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐
│              ORIGIN STORAGE TIER 1: AWS S3                      │
├─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┤
│ • Movie files (MP4/HLS/DASH formats)                            │
│ • High-resolution thumbnails & posters                          │
│ • Subtitles (multiple languages)                                │
│ • Backup & archival storage                                     │
│ • Cross-region replication for disaster recovery                │
└─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘
```

### **Why CDN for Movies?**
- **Low Latency**: Users download from nearest edge server
- **Bandwidth Optimization**: Origin server traffic reduced by 80-90%
- **Geographic Load Distribution**: Automatic failover between regions
- **DDoS Protection**: Built-in security at edge
- **Cost Efficiency**: Reduced origin bandwidth costs
- **Scalability**: Handle traffic spikes without origin overload

### **Streaming Formats**
- **Progressive Download**: MP4 for small files
- **Adaptive Bitrate**: HLS (HTTP Live Streaming) for quality adaptation
- **Alternative**: DASH (Dynamic Adaptive Streaming over HTTP)

