## 8. FILE STORAGE ARCHITECTURE

```
┌─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐
│         TIERED FILE STORAGE SYSTEM                      │
├─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┤
│
│ TIER 1: CDN (Hot Storage)
│ ├─ Popular movies (viewed in last 7 days)
│ ├─ New releases
│ ├─ Trending content
│ └─ Low latency, high cost
│
│ TIER 2: S3 Standard (Warm Storage)
│ ├─ All current movie files
│ ├─ Recently accessed
│ ├─ TTL: 30-90 days
│ └─ Medium latency, medium cost
│
│ TIER 3: S3 Glacier (Cold Storage)
│ ├─ Archived movies (not streaming)
│ ├─ Compliance backups
│ ├─ TTL: 1+ year
│ └─ High latency, very low cost
│
└─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘

Storage Lifecycle Policy:
├─ Days 0-7: CDN + S3 Standard
├─ Days 7-30: S3 Standard only (auto remove from CDN)
├─ Days 30-90: S3 Standard + S3 Intelligent-Tiering
├─ Days 90+: S3 Glacier (automatic after 90 days)
└─ Years 1+: S3 Glacier Deep Archive
```

